# Beregovaya, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Beregovaya () is a rural locality (a selo) in Kabansky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 346 as of 2010. There are 6 streets.
Geography
Beregovaya is located  southeast of Kabansk (the district's administrative centre) by road. Nyuki is the nearest rural locality.
